                <h5><b>Refund</b></h5>
                <p>Q. How can a refund for a cancelled ticket be obtained?</p>
                <p1>A.In order to get the refund, passengers with e-Tickets must file an online TDR within two days of the certificate issuance. They must also send the certificate to IRCTC by post. Passengers with counter tickets should send the certificate to IRCTC by post.</p1>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h5><b>Flight Delays and Cancellations</b></h5>
                <p>Q. Will I be contacted in advance if my flight is delayed, preponed or cancelled?</p>
                <p1>A. If you have provided us with your SMS-capable mobile phone number while booking, then FlyFriendly will notify you in advance through an SMS on your mobile phone. Passengers will also be sent the revised itinerary on their registered email address. We strongly recommend all passengers to provide us with their correct phone number and email address.</p1>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h5><b>Pre-paid Baggage</b></h5>
                <p>Q. What is the pre-paid excess baggage slab and how can i book it?</p>
                <p1>A. Passengers can book pre-paid excess baggage up to 1 hour prior to the scheduled departure of their domestic flight and 2 hour prior to the scheduled departure of their International flight, on the Website or through FlyFriendly’s call centre.</p1>
            </div>
        </div><br /><br />
